  "img": "icons/svg/d20-grey.svg",
  "description": "<p>Some tips on using the background table: </p><ul><li><p>There is some overlap of assets between backgrounds. If you use this table to generate characters in a co-op or guided game with other players, feel free to reroll a result with duplicates, or swap the matching asset for another of your choosing.</p></li><li><p>Some backgrounds are straightforward — if you've played other fantasy RPGs. you likely have a good understanding of what role a Ranger or Paladin embodies. Others are more evocative. Not sure what role a Cloak or Reaver might play in your world? Take a moment to envision it.</p></li><li><p>If you prefer to customize, go for it! For example, if magic does not exist in your version of the Ironlands, swap a ritual for another asset of your choosing.</p></li><li><p>The Loyalist asset — marked with an asterisk(*) — is meant for co-op or guided play with allies. If you are playing solo, swap this asset for one of your choosing.</p></li><li><p>This table includes two bonus assets that were only released in digital form: Commander and Lorekeeper. To add those assets to your collection, visit the downloads page to grab the latest print-and-play version of the Ironsworn asset deck.</p></li></ul>",
